team11.core

Class MainEntry

  • java.lang.Object
    • team11.core.MainEntry

  • public class MainEntry
extends java.lang.Object

    This class provides the main entry point for an implementation of an AI agent to play Angry Birds through the extension, provided by AIBirds.org, that must be enabled in Google's Chrome web browser. The specified agent to load must extend the Team11Agent abstract class; otherwise this will immediately terminate with the corresponding error code. Refer to the documentation for the Team11Agent on the specific requirements for implementing the agent.

    Command-line Parameters

    This application uses command-line parameters to adjust what will be loaded and how it will behave while running the agent.

    Options for team11.jar

    Option(s)Function(s)
    -a --agent [path]Required to specify your implementation of the agent which must extend the team11.core.agent.Team11Agent.
    -d --debug[optional] Sets the debugging for the agent to print out all debugging information when calling the internal debug(String) method. Default the debugging is set to false; not to print.
    -h --help[optional] If present, all other parameters are ignored and the usage for the jar file is printed to standard output, System.out.
    -l --log [path][optional] Sets the log file to be appended to when calling the internal log(String) method. Default prints to System.out.
    -s --show[optional] Shows the debugging screen capture frame.

    Example Usage

     [file system]
   rootfolder
     +-- team11
     |     +-- agent
     |           +-- MyAgent.class          // Must extend the Team11Agent!
     +-- team11.jar
     +-- log.txt
 [command prompt]
 %rootfolder> java -jar team11.jar -d -a team11\agent\MyAgent.class -l log.txt

    This execution will; (1) turns ON debugging with the option "-d", (2) load the specified agent based on the path following the "-a" option, and (3) set the log output file to the path following the "-l" option.
